description:
&lt;p&gt;GP Health Partners is supporting Banstead Primary Care Network (PCN) in the recruitment of a PCN Care Coordinator. The role involves working closely with Banstead PCN practices and the wider multidisciplinary comunity teams. The role will be pivotal in ensuring all patients receive the best possible care and service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Care Coordinators role will support member practices in coordinating key activity including access to services, advice, and information, and ensuring health and care planning is proactive, supportive and patient-centred. The role will include supporting digital initiatives and includes responsibilities for the co-ordination of the patient’s journey through primary care and the wider health and care system.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Care coordinators will be expected to work closely with the PCN Operations Manager and Clinical Director in fulfilling and developing their role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Previous applicants need not apply.&lt;/p&gt;
